Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Ping Zhao

2023-03-09

My meme

My meme is one of those final scenes from the movie Casablanca. The meme itself and the culture of meme are very new to me. I have not get used to or familiar with it. Therefor I have chosen the meme from one of my favorite movies to start with.

my_meme

library(magick)

#square one
final_scene <- image_read("https://cdn.quotesgram.com/img/4/23/86248399-2389aed455b9ba548413e19817666d26.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

#square two
movie_text <- image_blank (width = 500,
                           height = 750,
                           color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Final Scene\nCasablanca",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Eras Bold ITC",
                 gravity = "center")

#appending images
movie_vector <- c(final_scene, movie_text)
  image_append(movie_vector)

#save image
meme <- movie_vector
  image_write(meme,"my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

The meme called a rocky planet just caught my impression at the first glance and along with other three(one of those memes is also GIF format) memes of similar styles. I think this may be a kind of humor rather than too serious as My meme above.

my_animation

library(magick)

#retrieve URLs of four images and create 4 different frames
meme1<-image_read("https://i.imgflip.com/2373dw.jpg")%>%
  image_scale(800)
meme2<-image_read("https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP.DAQNhsndM2ag-Jt5uUmiFgAAAA?pid=ImgDet&rs=1")%>%
  image_scale(800)
meme3<-image_read("https://media.tenor.com/images/36c99c06bca27d6f057906aa8e893db9/tenor.gif")%>%
  image_scale(800)
meme4<-image_read("https://i.imgflip.com/2492ga.jpg")%>%
  image_scale(800)


#combine 4 frames together and create animation
frames<-c(meme1,meme2,meme3,meme4)

frames %>%
  image_animate(fps=1)

#save animated GIF
animation<-frames
image_write(animation,"my_animation.gif")
